IF.EXIST  file/path/volume nameThis command tests to see whether the specified file, path or volume exists.If the 'pathname' (which may include wildcards) is omitted, it is promptedfor.  The following return codes will be set in the {status} variable :-        0 - File/path/volume exists and is accessible        4 - File/path/volume was not found     Else - Appropriate GS/OS return code (a message will be issued also)Note that a non-zero return code will terminate an EXEC file unless the'UNSET EXIT' command has been issued.Example :-unset exit              ;* Survive non-zero return codes in EXEC filesIF.EXIST /RAM5if {status} == 0 ; rename /RAM5 /R ; endCopyright by Peter Watson, December 1988.